            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EIn%20looking%20back%20on%20his%20long%20life%2C%20David%20could%20highlight%20five%20attitudes%20that%20helped%20him%20not%20to%20worry%2C%20or%20%22fret%20not%2C%22%20as%20the%20King%20James%20Version%20reads%20(Psalm%2037%3A1).%20In%20common%20language%2C%20we%20might%20say%20%22sweat%20not%22%20because%20the%20original%20word%20used%20means%20%22to%20be%20under%20heat%20or%20pressure.%22%20When%20you%20are%20walking%20through%20a%20fiery%20trial%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20that%20you%20learn%20how%20to%20%22fret%22%20or%20%22sweat%22%20not!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20first%20thing%20you've%20got%20to%20do%20is%20%22trust%20in%20the%20Lord%22%20(v.%203)%2C%20or%20have%20an%20inward%20confidence%20that%20God%20is%20going%20to%20bring%20you%20through%20to%20the%20other%20side.%20With%20a%20conviction%20in%20your%20heart%20that%20God%20is%20on%20your%20side%20and%20wants%20to%20do%20you%20good%2C%20you%20can%20face%20anything.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESecond%2C%20you%20must%20%22delight%20in%20the%20Lord%22%20(v.%204)%2C%20or%20make%20the%20Lord%20%22delicious%22%20to%20you.%20Just%20as%20a%20son%20enjoys%20his%20father's%20company%2C%20so%20you%20must%20enjoy%20your%20heavenly%20Father's%20company.%20Are%20you%20truly%20delighted%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20Him%2C%20%22tasting%22%20of%20His%20goodness%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThird%2C%20you%20must%20%22commit%20everything%20you%20do%20to%20the%20Lord%22%20(v.%205)%2C%20or%20roll%20your%20problem%20onto%20Him%2C%20acknowledging%20Him%20as%20the%20only%20One%20who%20can%20carry%20your%20heavy%20burden.%20If%20you%20commit%20your%20problem%20to%20Him%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20option%20of%20taking%20it%20back!%20It%20is%20too%20heavy%20for%20you%3B%20you%20cannot%20carry%20it%20in%20your%20own%20strength.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFourth%2C%20you%20must%20%22be%20still%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20Lord%22%20(v.%207).%20This%20implies%20rest%2C%20not%20continually%20magnifying%20Satan's%20attack%20through%20your%20speech.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFinally%2C%20you%20must%20%22wait%20patiently%20for%20Him%20to%20act%22%20(v.%207)%2C%20keeping%20a%20constant%20sense%20of%20expectation%20that%20your%20miracle%20is%20right%20around%20the%20corner.%20It's%20never%20easy%20or%20pleasant%20to%20simply%20wait%2C%20but%20it%20is%20the%20key%20to%20seeing%20God%20move%20on%20your%20behalf.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETrust%2C%20delight%2C%20commit%2C%20be%20still%2C%20and%20wait.%20Your%20fretting%20will%20disappear%2C%20and%20God%20will%20bring%20the%20victory!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
